  "commentary": "With SPX at 6514.88 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6500 (-9.7B) and positive gamma cluster around 6525 (+3.7B), dealers are caught in a critical hedging zone where they'll amplify any directional move. The recent GEX surge in breakout regime means dealers are aggressively short gamma and will be forced buyers on any push higher toward 6525 or sellers on breaks back toward 6500, creating whipsaw conditions.\n\nWatch 6500 as the key inflection - a break below triggers dealer selling into 6400 support, while a sustained move above 6525 forces dealer buying that could accelerate upside momentum in this amplifying regime.",
